\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall hold final authority for logical access decisions affecting County information systems.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall exercise the Local Agency Security Officer (LASO) designation under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Data Governance and Classification Policy) for access decisions involving Criminal Justice Information (CJI).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall authorize each type of remote access and wireless access prior to permitting connections.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall approve shared,
 group,
 and emergency accounts based on documented operational necessity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall review shared,
 group,
 and emergency account approvals at least annually.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall adjudicate access decisions for High-Risk Individuals as defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
County Manager
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall approve access control policy exceptions that exceed the IT Director's delegated authority per 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Policy Implementation,
 Enforcement,
 and Legal Alignment).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assistant IT Director
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall maintain the account-type registry and the access control matrix required under this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall operate the periodic access recertification program defined in Section 6.9.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall ensure that information systems implement the technical access controls required by this policy,
 including account disablement automation,
 device lock,
 session termination,
 and unsuccessful-logon handling.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
May approve operational access exceptions within the Operational Exception Tier defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Department Heads
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall validate the specific need-to-know for personnel under their authority.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall ensure access requests are commensurate with assigned job duties.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall complete periodic access recertification reviews for systems under their data ownership within the cadence defined in Section 6.9.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall notify the IT Director within one (1) business day of identifying access that is no longer justified.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Human Resources
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall serve as the Authoritative Source for personnel status changes affecting logical access.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall notify the IT Director of terminations,
 transfers,
 and High-Risk Individual determinations in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:2.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
All County Personnel
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall not share credentials,
 authentication tokens,
 or access devices with any other person.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall not elevate privileges beyond those authorized for their assigned role by any means,
 direct or indirect.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall not bypass,
 disable,
 or circumvent access control mechanisms.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall report known or suspected credential compromise to the IT Director within one (1) hour of discovery,
 consistent with CJIS Security Policy v6.0:
 Section IR-6(a) (Incident Reporting).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Compliance with this policy is mandatory for all individuals with logical access to Elko County information systems.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assessment
\series default
:
 Adherence to this policy shall be assessed as part of the annual policy review and maturity scoring process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.07"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Annual Policy Review and Maturity Scoring) and through the periodic access recertification reviews defined in Section 6.9.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Enforcement
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall enforce this policy. Violations constitute non-compliance subject to the enforcement framework defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Exceptions to this policy shall be processed in accordance with the exception management framework defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 Oral exceptions are not valid.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Constraint
\series default
:
 Exceptions affecting access to systems that process,
 store,
 or transmit CJI shall route through the CJI Exceptions provisions of 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 which require written approval of the IT Director (as LASO) and,
 where applicable,
 written approval by the CJIS Systems Agency (CSA) or CJIS Systems Officer (CSO).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Universal Applicability
\series default
:
 These standards apply to all access to County information systems regardless of location or work arrangement,
 including remote work and official travel.
\end_layout

